genresAdvancedInfo.name: spanish blues
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Spanish blues is a style of music that blends traditional blues with Spanish influences. It often incorporates elements of flamenco, Latin rhythms, and Spanish guitar techniques. Spanish blues artists may sing in English or Spanish and may use a variety of instruments, including electric and acoustic guitars, harmonicas, and percussion. Some notable Spanish blues musicians include Raimundo Amador, Miguel Rios, and Los Deltonos.
